The men’s under-20 rugby world championship scheduled for Italy in June and July “will not take place this year because of the current impact of the Covid-19 pandemic,” World Rugby announced on Wednesday. Italy had also been scheduled to host the tournament last year before it was cancelled. “The decision was taken in consultation with the potential hosts and participating federations, taking into account all aspects from the financial impact to the consequences on the health of the players,” said the statement. “World Rugby is currently working with regions and federations to identify regional competitions that can be held in a safe environment, reflecting the international federation’s ambition to develop high-level competition models for future rugby stars,” the statement continued. Vanguard News Nigeria The coronavirus is disrupting sport around the world with the Moto Grand Prix in Qatar and Thailand postponed, a host of football matches put off to a later date and increasing concerns surrounding the Tokyo Olympics later this year. The virus has already cast a long shadow over the start… March 2, 2020 In "Sports" The ninth edition of the Rugby World Cup is currently taking place in Japan, which is the first time the tournament has been held in Asia. October 9, 2019 In "News" World Rugby on Thursday announced details of a $100 million coronavirus relief package aimed at supporting the global game and mitigating the impact of the coronavirus pandemic on the sport. A statement from the global governing body said the strategy reflected its commitment to leading the sport through its "greatest… April 16, 2020 In "Sports"